ger (Sastrulu) joined the staff of the Zemindarni's establishment. He has been a manager for the last fifteen years, during which period he has dhown a large saving, and has thus saved the estate from decay and ruin. He is spoken of very highly by the French Governor, and also by the Judge of Yanam...''}}\nHe later went on to become a landlord in Yanam and his popularity later paved way for his plunge into Yanam politics. His prominence can be understood from the incident of his request to obtain authorization to elect 2 members of Administration of committee of Vishnu and Siva Temples, replacing late Counomreddy Kroustama and Marla-P\u00e9rousomayazoulou was accepted by Clement-Thomas, then Governor of [[French India]] on 21 Sepetember 1894<ref>Journal Officiel des \u00e9tablissements fran\u00e7ais dans l'Inde, 1894.</ref>.\n\n==Political career==\nSastroulou was one of [[Bezawada Bapa Naidou]]'s  four councillors in the \"Conseil Local de Yanaon\" between 1928 and 1931 and later on under [[Kamichetty Venugopala Rao Naidou]] from 1931\u20131934. He had been one of the Judge Advocate (''Assesseur appel\u00e9s'') for the [[Criminal law|criminal court]] of Yanaon andgot elected as Councillor<ref>Journal Officiel des \u00e9tablissements fran\u00e7ais dans l'Inde, 1928.</ref>. After murder of Bapanaya Naidou few years later, Sastroulou stepped away from politics permanently.\n\nHe was married to Bouloussou Souryapracassamma (\u0c38\u0c42\u0c30\u0c4d\u0c2f\u0c2a\u0c4d\u0c30\u0c15\u0c3e\u0c36\u0c2e\u0c4d\u0c2e ''S\u016bryaprak\u0101\u015bamma''), daughter of Kala Latchminarayana and Kala Sodemma of [[Nadipudi]] village near [[Narasapur]] in [[West Godavari district]]. She is sister of former minister of [[Madras]] and [[Andhra Pradesh]], [[Kala Venkata Rao]]. The couple had three sons. Sastroulou is co-brother of [[Sripada Krishnamurty Sastry]], the first poet laureate of Andhra Pradesh through his wife Sripada Venkata Ratnamba (n\u00e9e Kala).\n\n==Death==\nSastroulou died at his ancestral house at Yanaon, situated in ruelle de Zalidinquy (Jaladanki street), Yanaon on 13 September 1941.<ref>Death Certificate issued by Municipality of Yanam.</ref>\n\n==Titles Held==\n* Diwan of [[Manyam Zamindari]] of Yanaon, from 1888 to 1941\n* Judge Advocate (Assesseur) for Criminal Court of Yanaon during 1917, 1918, 1919, 1920 and 1934\n\n==Offices held==\n{{s-start}}\n{{s-gov}}\n{{succession box|before=KALLA Vingata-Rattinom| title=Conseiller local de [[Yanam, French India|Yanaon]] | after=TOTA Narasinhassoimy | years=10 June 1928\u20131934 }}\n{{s-end}}\n\n== See also ==\n* [[Telugu people]]\n* [[Bouloussou family]]\n* [[Municipal Administration in French India]]\n\n==References==\n{{Use dmy dates|date=September 2011}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Sastroulou, Bouloussou}}\n[[Category:1874 births]]\n[[Category:French Hindus]]\n[[Category:People from Yanam district]]\n[[Category:French India]]\n[[Category:Telugu politicians]]\n[[Category:1941 deaths]]\n[[Category:French people of Telugu descent]]\n[[Category:People from Yanam]]\n", "name_user": "Rodw", "label": "safe", "comment": "Disambiguating links toNarsapur(link changed toNarasapuram) usingDisamAssist.", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bouloussou_Soubramanion_Sastroulou"}
